= Papen appointed Chancellor!

Be it through the failures of the democratic parties to successfully form a government, an increasingly growing <span style="color: #954B00;">**NSDAP**</span>, or a combination of various factors, Hindenburg’s patience for the parties of the republic has finally reached its breaking point. Chancellor [+ old_chancellor +] is set to be dismissed, and with the powers invested in the presidency, Hindenburg’s presidential cabinet will soon to be created. Few people are willing to take up Hindenburg’s offer to the Chancellorship, with his stubbornly conservative tendencies and annoyance at all but his most ardent supporters. However, there is one man who is willing to accept the position: Franz von Papen, a hardline conservative and nationalist hailing from <span style="color: #000000;">**Zentrum**</span>’s fringe right. Although <span style="color: #000000;">**Zentrum**</span> as a party is mainly supportive of the Republic, Papen, smelling an opportunity to take power for his own benefit, has taken the offer to form the presidential cabinet. Hindenburg has recently made an offer to us in joining the Papen cabinet, and should we accept, we could even coax Hindenburg into considering the <span style="color: #954B00;">**NSDAP**</span> as a possible puppet.

- @reject: Hold firm, we do not follow the one with a knife on democracy’s neck.
- @accept: Accept the offer, and take our place alongside Papen.
- @tolerate: Negotiate with Hindenburg, merely offering tolerance to the Papen cabinet.

@reject
subtitle: Our loyalty to the Republic will not be shaken.
view-if: dvp_ideology = "Left"
