As expected, we will be a part of Papen’s cabinet, much to the dismay of the remaining republicans left in the nation. Many of our remaining voters, the few who could stomach our fervent shift towards anti-parliamentarianism and alignment with the far right, rally in support of our decision, but the rest of the political spectrum has denounced our presence in this emergency-borne cabinet. For our part, Hindenburg has slowly begun to shift his own perceptions on Hitler, beginning to see him as a potential marionette to control rather than an upstart meant to be crushed. Perhaps the <span style="color: #954B00;">**Nazis**</span> could be tamed to be less destructive towards its fellow nationalists, though, most likely, the <span style="color: #954B00;">**Nazis**</span> will probably try to attain power for themselves.

